{
  "stem": "3382.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all-- first of all, I dropped out from the Department of Agriculture on account of one professor, Lelesz, who was well known.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, you know, he took revenge on me for that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then when-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] in 1936, '37, when they restarted all the troubles in university-- and they made a what's called academic ghetto, the Jews had to sit on the left side, and so on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was already, at that time, assistant, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I, I-- 1936, in two years, I got scholarships from the university after I returned, which permitted me to drop most of the-- my tutoring and some other obligations.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] ones and twos passed all the exams, except one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The most stupid exam was a needed exam-- science exam.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One professor, who kept me all the time-- cutting me down, cutting keep me down.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And finally, I came, and I was, was complaining, complaining to my professor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I say, on this account-- on account of Professor [NON-ENGLISH], I wouldn't be able to, to graduate ever and ever.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because three times-- we were permitted to take the same exam from this same subject three times.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And three times, his paleontology, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] he flunked me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So of course, Professor Limanowski, my main professor, and Professor [NON-ENGLISH], my supporter, and [NON-ENGLISH], another, and [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH]-- they went to him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And later, I learned that he did it because Lelesz asked him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But anyway, he gave me a C on the condition that some other grades will be cut by 10%.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you say the Jewish students already, at that point, were separated from the--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not-- wasn't--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--separated.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was '36.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I graduated with, with honor.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
